it came out yesterday.

00:03:23.250 --> 00:03:25.050
I thought it was pretty timely.

00:03:25.050 --> 00:03:25.950
And it's true.

00:03:25.950 --> 00:03:28.500
If you write a good syllabus,
it should really clear up

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:34.860
a lot of, not the content, not
the understanding level issues

00:03:34.860 --> 00:03:37.230
students have, but the
issues with respect

00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:40.710
to when's the test, do
we have to know this,

00:03:40.710 --> 00:03:44.130
how will this be graded,
what's important?

00:03:44.130 --> 00:03:46.990
All those things should
be in your syllabus.

00:03:46.990 --> 00:03:49.590
So that's why that's there.

