00:34:56.000 --> 00:34:58.250
and they're not very useful.

00:34:58.250 --> 00:35:00.410
The ones on the right
are student-centered

00:35:00.410 --> 00:35:03.020
and they are generally useful.

00:35:03.020 --> 00:35:06.230
But there's some things wrong
with the things on the right.

00:35:06.230 --> 00:35:07.700
AUDIENCE: Understand.

00:35:07.700 --> 00:35:12.264
JANET RANKIN: Understand, yes.

00:35:12.264 --> 00:35:13.680
So what would you
write instead of

00:35:13.680 --> 00:35:17.370
understand the formal constructs
of physical design, whatever

00:35:17.370 --> 00:35:19.440
the heck that means?

00:35:19.440 --> 00:35:20.554
What might you use?

00:35:20.554 --> 00:35:22.250
AUDIENCE: Identify.

00:35:22.250 --> 00:35:24.170
JANET RANKIN: Identify.

00:35:24.170 --> 00:35:24.840
OK.

00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:30.510
That might be like a list,
