for your classes.

00:37:28.512 --> 00:37:29.720
So that's an important thing.

00:37:29.720 --> 00:37:32.480
You get to call all the shots.

00:37:32.480 --> 00:37:33.730
You get to make the decision.

00:37:33.730 --> 00:37:36.410
We can only guess about
what this person meant,

00:37:36.410 --> 00:37:38.090
and therefore, his
or her students

00:37:38.090 --> 00:37:40.420
can only guess about
what he or she means.

00:37:46.010 --> 00:37:50.870
So you have on your table this
hierarchy of Bloom's Taxonomy.

00:37:50.870 --> 00:37:55.460
It's often shown in this
triangle, this pyramid.

00:37:55.460 --> 00:38:01.310
There's a handout which has
exactly the same strata on it.

00:38:01.310 --> 00:38:06.140
And it just has some handy
dandy verbs associated with it.

00:38:06.140 --> 00:38:09.530
But Benjamin Bloom came up
with this classification

00:38:09.530 --> 00:38:15.390
of cognitive processes way
back when, in the 1950s.

00:38:15.390 --> 00:38:17.510
And it is this idea that
it is this pyramid, that

00:38:17.510 --> 00:38:20.840
at the base of the pyramid
are these ideas like remember.

00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:27.140
And those are basic cognitive
processes, remember, list.

00:38:27.140 --> 00:38:33.200
And then it moves up the pyramid
to things that require a higher

00:38:33.200 --> 00:38:35.890
level of cognitive processing.

00:38:35.890 --> 00:38:38.860
Rather than just pulling
facts out of storage

00:38:38.860 --> 00:38:41.110
and stating them, you're
going to do something

00:38:41.110 --> 00:38:42.730
with those facts.

00:38:42.730 --> 00:38:46.820
So as you go higher and
higher up the pyramid,

00:38:46.820 --> 00:38:49.090
note that he chose--

00:38:49.090 --> 00:38:53.860
really unfortunately-- to call
the second level understand.

00:38:53.860 --> 00:38:57.460
However, there are
words that can help you.

00:38:57.460 --> 00:39:00.880
If it really is understand
that you want to measure,

00:39:00.880 --> 00:39:03.400
there's words that describe
that a little bit better.

00:39:03.400 --> 00:39:04.990
They're in your
table, and they're

00:39:04.990 --> 00:39:09.280
also in that second
table that I handed out.

00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:11.650
So arrange, list, label.

00:39:11.650 --> 00:39:16.310
For understand-- describe,
relate, recognize, explain,

00:39:16.310 --> 00:39:17.020
those things.

00:39:17.020 --> 00:39:17.520
Gordon.

